<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861204-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Hanna Will Buy Ohio Concern</HL><DD> 12/04/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HNMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   M.A. Hanna Co. said it agreed to buy closely held Burton Rubber Processing Inc., Burton, Ohio.    The price wasn't disclosed.    The natural resources concern said Burton Rubber had about $90 million of sales in the year ended June 30. Burton Rubber makes compounds used by makers of rubber and plastic compounds; it employs about 400 workers. </TEXT></DOC>